                                                           LFI 

This vulnerability exist when any Web application includes a file without correctly sanitizing the input,
which allows the attacker to manipulate the input and inject part traversal characters and include other files from the Web server.

anyparameter=somelocalfile 

example 

any.com/index.php?referee=login.php

['file','document,folder','root,path','pg,style','pdf,template','php_path','doc']

['dest','redirect','uri,path','continue','url','window','next','data','reference','site','html','val','validate',
'domain','callback','return','page','feed','post','host','port','to','out','view','dir','show','navigation','open']
